      "content": "Panic attacks are a common response to stress, and it's likely that your chest tightness and shortness of breath are related to the travel stress and jet lag. However, it's always a good idea to take a few deep breaths and try to relax. If the symptoms persist, you can try some calming techniques like progressive muscle relaxation or visualization. But if you're feeling really overwhelmed, I'd recommend taking a few minutes to sit down and drink some water - and then, if you're feeling up to it, you can try a quick 10-minute walk outside to get some fresh air.",
