      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Dizziness is a common side effect of anxiety, but it's also possible that it's related to the flight itself, especially if you've been sitting for a long time. However, blood clots are unlikely to be the cause of your symptoms, especially if you're feeling anxious. If you're really concerned, you can try to get some gentle exercise, like stretching or yoga, to help loosen up your muscles. And if you're feeling up to it, you can try taking some ibuprofen to help with the dizziness and pain - just be sure to follow the instructions on the label.",
      "source": "target",
